{"name": "backscatter", "metadata": {"name": "backscatter", "version": "0.2.4", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 4 - Beta", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Natural Language :: English", "Programming Language :: Python", "Topic :: Security", "Topic :: Software Development :: Libraries"], "home_page": "https://backscatter.io", "license": "MIT", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["requests", "tabulate"], "summary": "Client to interact with Backscatter.io services.", "upload_time": 1549662911}, "documentation": ["# Python Backscatter\n\n```{image} https://readthedocs.org/projects/backscatter/badge/?version=latest\n:target: https://backscatterio.readthedocs.io/en/latest/?badge=latest\n```\n\n```{image} https://badge.fury.io/py/backscatter.svg\n:target: https://badge.fury.io/py/backscatter\n```\n\n```{image} https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-yellow.svg\n:target: https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT\n```\n\nThis is an abstract python library built on top of the [Backscatter] service. It is preferred that users use this library when implementing integrations or plan to use Backscatter within their code. The library includes a small client to interact with the API.\n\n## Quick Start\n\n**Install the library**:\n\n`pip install  backscatter` or `python setup.py install`\n\n**Save your configuration**:\n\n`backscatter setup --api-key <your-API-key>`\n\n**Search observations**:\n\n`backscatter observations --query 148.227.224.17`\n\n**Get Trends**:\n\n`backscatter trends --type port`\n\n**Enrich values**:\n\n`backscatter enrich --query 148.227.224.17`\n\n## Features\n\n- Run observation searches for ip, network, asn, country and ports\n- Get trend data for all data types\n\n## Changelog\n\n### 02-03-19\n\n- Feature: Support for port enrichment call\n\n### 02-01-19\n\n- Feature: Support proxies within the core library\n- Change: Adjust timeout to something more favorable to long queries\n\n### 01-29-19\n\n- Bugfix: Avoid errors on free account without observations\n\n### 01-21-19\n\n- Feature: Added enrichment support\n- Feature: Added JSON and table output formats\n- Change: Adjusted query type to be optional if value is mapped to a type\n\n### 01-13-19\n\n- Bugfix: Resolved undeclared var in client observations call\n\n### 01-12-19\n\n- Initial launch of the library\n\n[backscatter]: https://backscatter.io/\n"], "modules": [{"name": "backscatter", "documentation": ["Abstract API over the Backscatter API.", "!/usr/bin/env python"], "functions": [{"name": "backscatter.valid_date", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "date", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Check the input date and ensure it matches the format."]}, {"name": "backscatter.valid_ip", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "ip_address", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "strict", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Check if the IP address is valid."]}, {"name": "backscatter.detect_query", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "query", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Attempt to identify the query type being made."]}], "variables": [{"name": "backscatter.__author__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "backscatter.__copyright__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "backscatter.__credits__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "backscatter.__license__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "backscatter.__maintainer__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "backscatter.__email__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "backscatter.__status__", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "backscatter.RequestFailure", "bases": ["Exception"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Exception to capture a failed request."]}, {"name": "backscatter.InvalidResponse", "